The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 25 April is 41,801 (4,838.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 20 April, there were 126 new confirmed cases (14.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 13 April, there were 151 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 17% (25 fewer cases).
